cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this software or its results, please cite it as below."
title: "Open-Access Rail Entry: Creation or Cannibalisation? A causal-inference study of Lumo on the East Coast Main Line"
abstract: >-
  A reproducible, multi-method causal-inference study of whether open-access rail
  entry (Lumo, London-Edinburgh, launched 25 October 2021) grows the market or
  cannibalises the franchised incumbent, and how much of any growth is abstracted
  from air. Uses only open and public data.
type: software
authors:
